t, what about the hand-staring?","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.31177,0.054246,0.27868,0.058964,0.039659,0.037243,0.033673,0.03869,0.040851,0.040007,0.03839,0.027832],"unified_progress":[0.18751,0.062175,0.24565,0.081714,0.056936,0.055157,0.054255,0.061989,0.060128,0.049406,0.044231,0.040847]},{"section":9,"text":"I remember that some children with ASD might have repetitive behaviors or fixations, but staring at hands isn't a typical one.","dimension":6,"group":2,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.062882,0.12775,0.081446,0.11512,0.10833,0.098989,0.08988,0.080393,0.07173,0.063629,0.055415,0.044443],"unified_progress":[0.1132,0.11073,0.075994,0.10261,0.094109,0.1086,0.082377,0.078767,0.072459,0.065894,0.055092,0.040171]},{"section":10,"text":"Maybe it's a self-stimulatory behavior, which is common in ASD.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.047594,0.087363,0.096758,0.10079,0.1019,0.09827,0.095307,0.089436,0.081545,0.078232,0.066119,0.056689],"unified_progress":[0.057666,0.079528,0.093379,0.099616,0.099386,0.099386,0.095783,0.091195,0.084674,0.080737,0.06665,0.051999]},{"section":11,"text":"Are there other possibilities?","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.32978,0.054291,0.054499,0.06332,0.063578,0.063962,0.060571,0.067108,0.06758,0.062202,0.064647,0.048463],"unified_progress":[0.22352,0.086655,0.066732,0.065751,0.075072,0.072851,0.093797,0.078119,0.074062,0.058838,0.053772,0.050827]},{"section":12,"text":"Like language disorder without the social aspects?","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.044278,0.092095,0.069421,0.10692,0.10631,0.097114,0.097026,0.091879,0.085275,0.078939,0.071954,0.058788],"unified_progress":[0.055367,0.09489,0.072175,0.096412,0.10215,0.097642,0.094838,0.095283,0.089351,0.082203,0.069914,0.049777]},{"section":13,"text":"But the case mentions issues beyond just speech\u2014like concentration and social interaction.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.043509,0.083017,0.086864,0.088052,0.091147,0.093484,0.095066,0.095349,0.090674,0.087508,0.080501,0.064828],"unified_progress":[0.06139,0.078062,0.082088,0.085847,0.091818,0.09322,0.093688,0.096463,0.092034,0.091973,0.077292,0.056126]},{"section":14,"text":"Maybe a genetic disorder?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029542,0.066985,0.085614,0.094061,0.098627,0.097141,0.09844,0.097878,0.093961,0.09421,0.081251,0.062291],"unified_progress":[0.043506,0.075415,0.088994,0.10081,0.099472,0.097229,0.10064,0.095808,0.090125,0.088614,0.070635,0.048754]},{"section":15,"text":"Like Fragile X syndrome?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02859,0.064756,0.081281,0.091418,0.098851,0.10094,0.10197,0.099887,0.094449,0.091993,0.079917,0.065943],"unified_progress":[0.041876,0.072311,0.08782,0.09649,0.099521,0.1012,0.10078,0.097379,0.09109,0.086197,0.071044,0.054294]},{"section":16,"text":"That can present with autism-like symptoms, but would there be other signs like physical features?","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02362,0.057216,0.073622,0.085217,0.093832,0.098845,0.10541,0.10537,0.10157,0.099779,0.089398,0.066134],"unified_progress":[0.033348,0.060557,0.077341,0.086277,0.096595,0.10009,0.10205,0.10544,0.10167,0.10386,0.080721,0.052059]},{"section":17,"text":"The case doesn't mention those.","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.312,0.050809,0.051817,0.060838,0.062533,0.064574,0.063535,0.071809,0.071128,0.067417,0.068997,0.054545],"unified_progress":[0.20445,0.076665,0.065939,0.06595,0.076092,0.076213,0.094726,0.086268,0.082291,0.064696,0.055975,0.050732]},{"section":18,"text":"Another thought: Rett syndrome?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030913,0.068473,0.061694,0.097236,0.10419,0.098432,0.10106,0.1001,0.096745,0.090796,0.082976,0.067388],"unified_progress":[0.041897,0.082781,0.073443,0.099131,0.10581,0.10064,0.098394,0.099835,0.093563,0.084581,0.07103,0.048893]},{"section":19,"text":"But that's more common in girls, and usually involves regression after initial development, plus specific motor issues.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.021761,0.053261,0.068919,0.081595,0.092003,0.097864,0.10638,0.10839,0.10548,0.10264,0.094286,0.067429],"unified_progress":[0.032808,0.060971,0.076155,0.083801,0.096795,0.099286,0.10182,0.10748,0.10369,0.10497,0.082078,0.050154]},{"section":20,"text":"Since the child is a boy, Rett is less likely.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029089,0.06246,0.074475,0.082573,0.089906,0.097364,0.10005,0.10216,0.10024,0.098209,0.089578,0.073897],"unified_progress":[0.053317,0.082052,0.082835,0.084873,0.089014,0.090887,0.094161,0.095311,0.092314,0.093992,0.079768,0.061475]},{"section":21,"text":"Attention Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder (ADHD) could cause concentration issues, but the communication and social problems are more pronounced here.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032755,0.067527,0.07732,0.084078,0.089996,0.094276,0.099133,0.10058,0.096446,0.096608,0.088438,0.072841],"unified_progress":[0.042288,0.067626,0.078838,0.0856,0.09213,0.095943,0.098047,0.099952,0.09686,0.09863,0.083367,0.060719]},{"section":22,"text":"Nonverbal Learning Disorder?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031101,0.065566,0.078596,0.088025,0.09588,0.098873,0.10144,0.10063,0.095927,0.094149,0.082841,0.066972],"unified_progress":[0.038193,0.067714,0.085014,0.09493,0.098564,0.10172,0.10205,0.099831,0.094596,0.089927,0.073866,0.053593]},{"section":23,"text":"That might involve social difficulties and motor problems, but again, the hand-staring isn't a typical symptom.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02346,0.055625,0.07084,0.081596,0.090605,0.096509,0.1043,0.10616,0.10469,0.10154,0.094298,0.070379],"unified_progress":[0.032547,0.059148,0.075115,0.084277,0.094979,0.097773,0.10105,0.10573,0.10319,0.10684,0.084378,0.054976]},{"section":24,"text":"So going back to ASD.","dimension":12,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028675,0.059646,0.075865,0.084612,0.091971,0.09424,0.096278,0.096859,0.096979,0.095783,0.089428,0.089665],"unified_progress":[0.039663,0.06369,0.07509,0.087912,0.089314,0.090396,0.10104,0.093269,0.091249,0.096295,0.089599,0.082479]},{"section":25,"text":"The combination of language delay, social interaction problems, communication issues, and possible repetitive behavior (hand-staring) fits.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027573,0.057605,0.068903,0.077057,0.085461,0.09141,0.096587,0.09816,0.10113,0.10189,0.10176,0.092459],"unified_progress":[0.043856,0.056718,0.06706,0.07473,0.084192,0.092825,0.095173,0.099389,0.1013,0.10406,0.098136,0.082567]},{"section":26,"text":"The fact that the milestones are otherwise normal except language might still align with ASD since it's a spectrum.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033966,0.067799,0.077119,0.083172,0.088237,0.093227,0.094925,0.096256,0.095423,0.095986,0.089788,0.084103],"unified_progress":[0.061631,0.077091,0.077304,0.080315,0.084029,0.087923,0.089075,0.092907,0.091387,0.092202,0.087668,0.078469]},{"section":27,"text":"Some kids have delays in specific areas.","dimension":6,"group":2,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034051,0.068746,0.079606,0.087427,0.093778,0.097511,0.099526,0.098514,0.094325,0.092168,0.083667,0.070681],"unified_progress":[0.089708,0.07706,0.080315,0.083845,0.08703,0.089821,0.089645,0.092408,0.08647,0.086174,0.075339,0.062185]},{"section":28,"text":"I think the most likely diagnosis here is Autism Spectrum Disorder.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028125,0.053415,0.063882,0.070681,0.076159,0.080043,0.085408,0.088611,0.09414,0.098001,0.10594,0.15559],"unified_progress":[0.031795,0.042902,0.052005,0.063045,0.064963,0.074058,0.077893,0.084473,0.095745,0.10376,0.13533,0.17403]},{"section":29,"text":"The child presents with delayed language development, difficulty in communication and social interaction, and repetitive behavior (spending time staring at hands).","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042309,0.073755,0.07025,0.070807,0.076897,0.084455,0.088653,0.094001,0.096425,0.099186,0.10278,0.10048],"unified_progress":[0.046952,0.061418,0.064027,0.067675,0.075833,0.086925,0.088324,0.096975,0.10288,0.10754,0.1081,0.093347]},{"section":30,"text":"These symptoms are hallmark features of Autism Spectrum Disorder (ASD).","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036528,0.063203,0.070721,0.076823,0.081271,0.08321,0.087982,0.08965,0.091774,0.097476,0.098744,0.12262],"unified_progress":[0.041378,0.047303,0.057682,0.065772,0.072316,0.082048,0.085971,0.094006,0.098928,0.1049,0.11735,0.13235]},{"section":31,"text":"The absence of friends and challenges in making social connections further support this diagnosis.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.04225,0.076799,0.077763,0.079119,0.082949,0.087772,0.09047,0.093331,0.092883,0.093906,0.092315,0.090443],"unified_progress":[0.046101,0.06425,0.068311,0.073152,0.079451,0.087067,0.089052,0.096017,0.098969,0.10258,0.10167,0.093386]},{"section":32,"text":"While other conditions like language disorders or ADHD may contribute, the combination of social, communication, and repetitive behavior abnormalities strongly points to ASD.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030496,0.061496,0.072702,0.080326,0.086599,0.090234,0.094995,0.095929,0.09647,0.098364,0.096185,0.096202],"unified_progress":[0.034663,0.053539,0.065258,0.073788,0.081317,0.089034,0.092705,0.097856,0.10093,0.10547,0.10529,0.10015]},{"section":33,"text":"Other genetic disorders 